-- Noda Says He Will Run in Japan Ruling Party Leadership Race
-- B y   I s a b e l   R e y n o l d s   a n d   T a k a s h i   H i r o k a w a
-- 2012-09-07T08:40:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/noda-says-he-will-run-in-japan-ruling-party-leadership-race.html
Japanese Prime Minister  Yoshihiko
Noda  said he will run for re-election as head of the ruling
Democratic Party of Japan.  The DPJ meets on Sept. 21 to decide whether to keep Noda as
party standard bearer.  “I cannot leave these problems the country faces in an
unfinished state,” Noda said at a press conference today in
Tokyo. “I want to continue with my duties.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
